      • findEmployee

        public Employee findEmployee(java.lang.String id)
        Name: findEmployee
        This method seeks an employee. This method is to avoid that an employee will be created twice.
        Pre: The workers ArrayList must be initialized. workers!=null.
        Post: The employee was or wasn't found successfully.
        Parameters:
        id - String. Identification of the employee. id!="".
        Returns:
        find Employee. If the method find the employee, it will return it because you can't create the same user twice.
        But, if the method doesn't find the employee, it wouldn't return anything, it would be null and you can create the employee.

      • findEmployeePosition

        public int findEmployeePosition(java.lang.String id)
        Name: findEmployeePosition
        This method seeks the position in the workers ArrayList of an employee.
        Pre: The workers ArrayList must be initialized. workers!=null.
        Post: The position of the employee in the workers ArrayList was or wasn't found successfully.
        Parameters:
        id - String. Identification of the employee. id!="".
        Returns:
        index int. If the method find the position of the employee in the workers ArrayList, it will return the position where is that employee.
        But, if the method doesn't find the position of the employee, it will return -1.

      • hireEmployee

        public java.lang.String hireEmployee(java.lang.String name,
                                     java.lang.String id,
                                     double salary,
                                     int numberTshirt,
                                     int amountGoals,
                                     int averageGrade,
                                     int position,
                                     int team)
        Name: hireEmployee
        This method allows to create or hire a soccer player and added to the workers ArrayList.
        Pre: The workers ArrayList must be created. workers!=null.
        Post: The soccer player was created and hired successfully.
        Parameters:
        name - String. Name of the soccer player. name!="".
        id - String. Identification of the soccer player. id!="".
        salary - double. Salary of the soccer player. salary!=0.
        numberTshirt - int. Number of the tshirt of a soccer player.
        amountGoals - int. Amount of goals of a soccer player.
        averageGrade - int. Average grade of a soccer player.
        position - int. Number of the position chose by the player. position mayor o igual a 1 y menor o igual a 4.
        team - int. Which team, teamA or teamB. If team==1 is teamA, but if team==2 is teamB.
        Returns:
        message String. Message that confirm or deny if the soccer player was created and hired.
